text.__SUMMARY__:
Banksia porrecta, formerly known as Dryandra porrecta, is a shrub endemic to Western Australia.
An assessment of the potential impact of climate change on this species found that its range is likely to contract by between 50% and 80% by 2080, depending on the severity of the change.
text.References: "Banksia porrecta". FloraBase. Western Australian Government Department of Parks and Wildlife.
